      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 90.62
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Yes, I can certainly hear you!",
      "at_sec": 91.06
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Tell me a long stay of the lighthouse keeper",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 98.43
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Elias had lived on the jagged tooth of rock known as Needle Reach for forty years, his life measured by the rhythmic rotation of the great brass lens.",
      "at_sec": 99.44
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Each evening, he would climb the spiral stairs with a heavy bucket of oil and a lantern, performing the ritual of polishing the glass until it sparkled against the salt spray.",
      "at_sec": 100.08
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The only sounds were the crashing of the Atlantic waves below and the steady, mechanical heartbeat of the ticking clockwork gears.",
      "at_sec": 100.52
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "During the long winter months, the fog would roll in so thick that the world beyond the railing ceased to exist, leaving him in a solitude so profound he began to talk to the gulls as if they were old friends.",
      "at_sec": 101.37
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "He found comfort in the meticulous nature of his duties: the cleaning of the wicks, the logging of weather patterns in leather-bound books, and the constant vigilance over the beam that guided sailors through the graveyard of ships.",
      "at_sec": 102.19
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "To Elias, the light was not just a signal; it was a promise kept to every sailor lost at sea, a steady pulse of safety in a wild and unpredictable world.",
      "at_sec": 102.84
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Up",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 151.67
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Up you go!",
      "at_sec": 152.08
